BLOK main
  say "Hello world"
END

Explanation:

BLOK main â€¦ END defines the top-level block that runs first.

say "Hello world" prints the text to the console.

When run through your BLOKS interpreter in Python, it will output:

Hello world

You can also add a line break or multiple messages by adding more say commands:

BLOK main
  say "Hello world"
  say "Welcome to BLOKS!"
END
When run through your BLOKS interpreter in Python, it will output:

Hello world
Welcome to BLOKS!